    <abstract id="aspace_1e428b3390341941ca3132638848e590">The Herbert and Francis Bernstein Collection on the CIMS Academic Computing Facility (dated 1956-1996) consists of materials created by Hebert and Francis Bernstein in the course of their work at the Courant Institute of Mathematical Sciences (CIMS) Computer Facility. Materials include class notes, course bulletins, newsletters, clippings, operating brochures for computers at the facility, publications, staff directories, and log books for the Ultracomputer.</abstract>
    <physloc id="aspace_42ffabb73597b62abe1ea59c24553f6f" label="Location Note">Materials are stored offsite and advance notice is required for use. Please request materials at least two business days prior to your research visit to coordinate access.</physloc>
    <langmaterial id="aspace_db974cf4cd90b9874c7d00d85514eb21">Materials are in English.</langmaterial>
  </did>
  <scopecontent id="aspace_1da84f9577072fea933b1b7a8694e50b">
    <head>Scope and Contents</head>
<p>The Herbert and Francis Bernstein Collection on the CIMS Academic Computing Facility (dated 1956-1996) consists of materials created by Hebert and Francis Bernstein in the course of their work at the Courant Institute of Mathematical Sciences (CIMS) Computer Facility. Materials include class notes, course bulletins, newsletters, clippings, operating brochures for computers at the facility, publications, staff directories, and log books for the Ultracomputer.</p>  </scopecontent>
  <arrangement id="aspace_449a2f8eaa7c7b4e89b147d05638e9c2">
    <head>Arrangement</head>
<p>This collection has not been arranged by an archivist. The materials are arranged in the order in which they were received from the donor.</p>  </arrangement>
  <appraisal id="aspace_f0323ed521c51549d637f71d2f452d42">
    <head>Appraisal</head>
<p>Duplicate copies of publications were appraised out during acquisition.</p>  </appraisal>
  <accessrestrict id="aspace_39b1744a6cd969f8cf49c1eb16f2b277">
    <head>Conditions Governing Access</head>
<p>Materials are open without restrictions.</p>  </accessrestrict>
  <userestrict id="aspace_b78db2410cb6e98eec259f8886d36e4e">
    <head>Conditions Governing Use</head>
<p>This collection is protected by copyright and/or related rights. You are free to use materials in the collection in any way that is permitted by the copyright and related rights legislation that applies to your use. For other uses you need to obtain permission from the rights-holder(s).</p>  </userestrict>
  <acqinfo id="aspace_cd8abf5b9d4a03c1a0d8315cd8f75d8a">
    <head>Immediate Source of Acquisition</head>
<p>The collection was transferred from the Courant Institute Library in the summer of 2023 to the New York University Archives when the Courant Institute Library closed. The accession number associated with this transfer is 2026.017.</p>  </acqinfo>
  <custodhist id="aspace_a35b2e47255e924bf95cd9ce294f2471">
    <head>Custodial History</head>
<p>This collection was transferred to the Courant Institute Library in November 2020 by the Bernstein family, but there is no deed of gift.</p>  </custodhist>
  <prefercite id="aspace_a16afb5fdb0ae2e777dc33865357ea56">
    <head>Preferred Citation</head>
<p>Identification of item, date; Herbert and Francis Bernstein Collection on the CIMS Academic Computing Facility; MC 390; box number; folder number or item identifier; New York University Archives, New York University.</p>  </prefercite>
  <processinfo id="aspace_223dedb35e00c0902e3c9aa06b89fa45">
    <head>Processing Information</head>
<p>At the time of accessioning materials were rehoused in archival boxes. Loose materials were foldered in archival folders. Materials were described on the collection-level with a folder-level inventory.</p>  </processinfo>
  <bioghist id="aspace_89e7bdf0e96b297b81c4422f6e5b2fe5">
    <head>Biographical Note</head>
<p>Herbert and Francis Bernstein worked at the Courant Institute of Mathematical Sciences (CIMS) Computing Facility. Herbert J. Bernstein's research focused on applied computing, especially laboratory automation, data communications, databases, and robotics. He also produced the NYU Computer Center Newsletter.</p>  </bioghist>
